    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Going to maker events</h2>\n<p>The rain was hammering on the windows at the hackspace one cold February evening in 2018, a few of us were huddled under the heat lamp working out what to do for MakerFaire and MakeFest.</p>\n<p>We were determined to show up to these events as exhibitors - we just needed to find out what. It had to be hands on, something people would come to, and leave with something of value.</p>\n<h2>To Bee or Not to bee</h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/85e8014903db00f3ef8398078246dfdf/d533d/bollard.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Bee Bollards can be found in Manchester\"\n        title=\"Bee Bollards can be found in Manchester\"\n        src=\"/static/85e8014903db00f3ef8398078246dfdf/1c72d/bollard.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/85e8014903db00f3ef8398078246dfdf/a80bd/bollard.jpg 148w,\n/static/85e8014903db00f3ef8398078246dfdf/1c91a/bollard.jpg 295w,\n/static/85e8014903db00f3ef8398078246dfdf/1c72d/bollard.jpg 590w,\n/static/85e8014903db00f3ef8398078246dfdf/d533d/bollard.jpg 599w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Bee Bollards can be found in Manchester</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The symbol of Manchester is the worker bee - a reflection back to the industrial revolution when Manchester was full of working mills and a hive of industreous activity. It still is, but the mills are now trendy flats and the industreous activity is usually over a latte or foosball table.</p>\n<p>The bee emblem can be found all over the city, including on bollards, and it may well have been the <em>inexplicable</em> appearance of a bollard in the space that gave me the idea that we should do something featuring the bee.</p>\n<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n<p>So using the laser cutter, I made a quick bee and using an LED and battery, we had a prototype.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/012da256d7f8c8c4344bf2063b3347a1/65069/proto.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"My prototype bee wasn&#39;t much, but it had the effect of firing us up!\"\n        title=\"My prototype bee wasn&#39;t much, but it had the effect of firing us up!\"\n        src=\"/static/012da256d7f8c8c4344bf2063b3347a1/1c72d/proto.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/012da256d7f8c8c4344bf2063b3347a1/a80bd/proto.jpg 148w,\n/static/012da256d7f8c8c4344bf2063b3347a1/1c91a/proto.jpg 295w,\n/static/012da256d7f8c8c4344bf2063b3347a1/1c72d/proto.jpg 590w,\n/static/012da256d7f8c8c4344bf2063b3347a1/a8a14/proto.jpg 885w,\n/static/012da256d7f8c8c4344bf2063b3347a1/65069/proto.jpg 892w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">My prototype bee wasn&#39;t much, but it had the effect of firing us up!</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>With this prototype, my mind was pretty fixed on laser cutting some template and having some way of people assembling and colouring in the bee.</p>\n<p>However, the brilliant idea someone else had was to make a PCB - something I'd never done before and something which was way out of my skill league.</p>\n<p>The idea was instantly attractive, a we wouldn't need to work out how to secure the electronics to the bee, and <a href=\"https://mightyohm.com/files/soldercomic/FullSolderComic_EN.pdf\">soldering is easy</a>.</p>\n<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n<h2>Making a PCB</h2>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e48635e1fce79075756b053d5abcec7e/30cf6/protos.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 93.24324324324323%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The prototypes arriving was a huge highlight - they looked SO GOOD!\"\n        title=\"The prototypes arriving was a huge highlight - they looked SO GOOD!\"\n        src=\"/static/e48635e1fce79075756b053d5abcec7e/1c72d/protos.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e48635e1fce79075756b053d5abcec7e/a80bd/protos.jpg 148w,\n/static/e48635e1fce79075756b053d5abcec7e/1c91a/protos.jpg 295w,\n/static/e48635e1fce79075756b053d5abcec7e/1c72d/protos.jpg 590w,\n/static/e48635e1fce79075756b053d5abcec7e/a8a14/protos.jpg 885w,\n/static/e48635e1fce79075756b053d5abcec7e/30cf6/protos.jpg 956w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The prototypes arriving was a huge highlight - they looked SO GOOD!</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>I was very fortunate that a friend at the space was willing to teach me how to use KiCad software to design PCBs.</p>\n<p>The idea was a hexagonal board, with the bee in the middle. It seemed easy enough with the help of someone experienced, but when I tried to do it alone I quickly got stuck! With someone knowledgable neaby, I found out about ENIG - using gold on the front of the board which could be used to make a beautiful effect.</p>\n<p>I made a rough first design, and when this was checked over (turns out I'd shorted out a few bits, this would have made the battery become a small heater) and sorted out, we were ready to go ahead and get a small batch made by Elecrow.</p>\n<p>We soldered some up, and they worked! It felt like we were really onto something here.</p>\n<h2>Refining and pricing</h2>\n<p>During testing we found that the hole in the middle, used to wear the board as a badge, interfered with the depth of the battery holder meaning it was tricky to wear it as a badge.</p>\n<p>We moved the hole to the top of the badge, and then did something scary - order 500 badges!</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/be464/soldered.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Soldered up badges - they looked so good\"\n        title=\"Soldered up badges - they looked so good\"\n        src=\"/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/1c72d/soldered.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/a80bd/soldered.jpg 148w,\n/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/1c91a/soldered.jpg 295w,\n/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/1c72d/soldered.jpg 590w,\n/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/a8a14/soldered.jpg 885w,\n/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/fbd2c/soldered.jpg 1180w,\n/static/f4f0160760f6e51f47df360100621bfb/be464/soldered.jpg 1191w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Soldered up badges - they looked so good</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>We booked our place at Maker Faire and rallied a team together.</p>\n<p>We also had to get parts:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LEDs, two per badge, plus some margin for error. We wanted a mix of colours so people could personalise their badge.</li>\n<li>Battery holders</li>\n<li>Batteries</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These were all costed out in order for us to set a price point - we had NO idea what people would pay for them, if they would pay at all.</p>\n<p>We figured that going for pocket money amounts would likely be successful, so we priced them at £4 for the kit, and £6 assembled - this way people who wanted to solder them could do so for under £5, but those that wanted to just buy one would pay a small premium.</p>\n<p>Risk assessments done (namely \"don't touch the shiny part of the soldering iron - you'll let go very quickly\" and \"don't eat the batteries\") we were good to go.</p>\n<p>Our attitude at this point was one of nerves and acceptance - we were totally okay if we didn't make our money back over the weekend. I know I defined a success as making our money back, and wouldn't be upset if there wasn't really the interest.</p>\n<p>We were agreed that we could go as low as £3 if we had to, so with a cash float, boxes of leaflets and promotional stuff for the space (as well as projects and a monitor showing a slideshow), we packed our stuff, and headed for Newcastle.</p>\n<h2>The event</h2>","frontmatter":{"title":"Teaching soldering with custom designed PCBee","featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/pcbees/"}},
